It cuts off because that last bit was part of my edit to (hopefully) save this article, and I frequently do that when using [DATA EXPUNGED], My logic being that whoever censors these documents is just as human and lazy as everyone else. [DATA EXPUNGED] is a way of showing that a large amount of text (paragraphs or pages) has been removed, and I've always imagined that if a line carried over onto the next page, it might be left behind by a lazy censor. Ever seen those leaked classified CIA documents? Like that.







